     4→// NOTE: This file is part of the “PaletteStream ETL Canvas” project.
     5→//
     6→// The TransformationWorker is a long-running background service that pulls raw data
     7→// “pigments” from an async source, applies a Strategy-pattern driven transformation,
     8→// performs data-quality checks, and then writes the curated result to the downstream
     9→// sink.  Throughout the process it broadcasts lifecycle events to any registered
    10→// observers, enabling real-time monitoring, alerting, and metrics collection.
    11→//
    12→// The worker is designed for high-throughput scenarios and can be hosted inside
    13→// Kestrel, a Worker Service container, or executed as a Hangfire recurring job.
    14→//
    15→// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
    16→// External NuGet packages assumed:
    17→//   - Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting
    18→//   - Microsoft.Extensions.Logging
    19→//   - System.Threading.Channels
    20→//   - Microsoft.Data.Analysis (optional; only referenced in models)
    21→// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
